HEADWORD: Unpray
<hw>Un*pray</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[1st pref.
<ets>un-</ets> + <ets>pray</ets>.]</ety> <def>To revoke or annul by
prayer, as something previously prayed for.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>
<rj><au>Sir M. Hale.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Unprayable</ent>⟦br⟧
